00:00:01.840 --> 00:00:04.850
Prof: Okay,
well I want to start by

00:00:04.850 --> 00:00:09.109
cleaning up a little bit of
stuff done near the end of last

00:00:09.109 --> 00:00:09.770
time.
 

00:00:09.770 --> 00:00:13.960
So I told you the whole thing
with magnetism is going to

00:00:13.960 --> 00:00:18.076
contain two parts,
just like with electricity,

00:00:18.076 --> 00:00:23.949
namely how do things react to a
magnetic field and how do things

00:00:23.949 --> 00:00:26.560
produce a magnetic field?
 

00:00:26.560 --> 00:00:29.758
Just like the electric charges,
electric charges produce

00:00:29.758 --> 00:00:32.840
electric fields and electric
charges react to electric

00:00:32.840 --> 00:00:33.480
fields.
 

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:36.890
So the first part is very easy
for magnetism.

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:41.749
The force of magnetism on a
charge q depends on its

00:00:41.749 --> 00:00:46.780
velocity, because if it doesn't
move, it doesn't feel it.

00:00:46.780 --> 00:00:49.355
And it depends on the magnetic
field, which I will denote by

00:00:49.355 --> 00:00:50.360
some symbol B.
 

00:00:50.360 --> 00:00:53.592
Then you can ask yourself,
"How am I going to get a

00:00:53.592 --> 00:00:55.590
vector out of two vectors?"
 

00:00:55.590 --> 00:00:58.815
namely the velocity and
B, and a natural

00:00:58.815 --> 00:01:01.130
candidate is the cross product.
 

00:01:01.130 --> 00:01:05.180
Now that doesn't mean that's
the right answer.

00:01:05.180 --> 00:01:07.706
For example,
I can multiply this by the

00:01:07.706 --> 00:01:11.563
absolute value of velocity
squared and that will still be a

00:01:11.563 --> 00:01:14.290
vector, because that's just a
scalar.

00:01:14.290 --> 00:01:16.391
Anyway, ignore that,
because that's not what

00:01:16.391 --> 00:01:16.879
happens.
 

00:01:16.879 --> 00:01:18.970
Nature is very kind and it's
just

00:01:18.970 --> 00:01:22.540
v x B.
 

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:24.486
And you got to know how to do
the cross products,

00:01:24.486 --> 00:01:24.769
okay?
 

00:01:24.769 --> 00:01:27.890
There are two rules you're
going to use all the time.

00:01:27.890 --> 00:01:31.406
One is the cross product,
which is for me the screwdriver

00:01:31.406 --> 00:01:33.218
rule,
that if you've got a vector

00:01:33.218 --> 00:01:35.349
v and you've got a vector
B,

00:01:35.349 --> 00:01:39.491
you turn the screwdriver from
v to B and the way

00:01:39.491 --> 00:01:43.090
it comes out is the direction of
the cross product.

00:01:43.090 --> 00:01:44.940
So everyone's doing that.
 

00:01:44.940 --> 00:01:47.560
You can also do it with your
hand.

00:01:47.560 --> 00:01:49.550
Have you seen all the rap guys?
 

00:01:49.550 --> 00:01:52.376
They're all computing cross
products, because there turns

00:01:52.376 --> 00:01:54.950
out to be a right hand rule and
a left hand rule.

00:01:54.950 --> 00:01:57.410
So you can do that,
or you can do this.

00:01:57.410 --> 00:02:00.980
Another one is whenever there's
a current or something,

00:02:00.980 --> 00:02:03.299
you don't know which way the
magnetic field is going,

00:02:03.299 --> 00:02:06.040
you're supposed to wrap your
hands around the current.

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:07.450
Now don't do this at home.
 

00:02:07.450 --> 00:02:10.777
Wrap it around the current,
and the thumb points the

00:02:10.777 --> 00:02:12.408
direction of the field.
 

00:02:12.408 --> 00:02:14.764
So whenever you have doubts
about which way something is

00:02:14.764 --> 00:02:16.322
going,
if you see something looping

00:02:16.322 --> 00:02:18.447
around,
wrap your four fingers around

00:02:18.447 --> 00:02:20.364
that loop,
and thumb will point in the

00:02:20.364 --> 00:02:21.470
direction of the answer.
 

00:02:21.470 --> 00:02:25.055
I've been using it a lot
without spelling it out for you,

00:02:25.055 --> 00:02:28.577
but you should know at least
the technical definition of

00:02:28.577 --> 00:02:29.729
cross product.
 

00:02:29.729 --> 00:02:32.663
Another thing is,
I didn't tell you anything

00:02:32.663 --> 00:02:33.620
