00:11:14.528 --> 00:11:17.554
But whenever we see a sine
theta and a lot of vectors,

00:11:17.554 --> 00:11:20.009
we know we're looking at a
cross product.

00:11:20.009 --> 00:11:23.096
And the cross product,
the vector formula for tau,

00:11:23.096 --> 00:11:27.412
is going to be written as
μ x B,

00:11:27.412 --> 00:11:33.957
and μ is a quantity
which is area vector times the

00:11:33.957 --> 00:11:39.755
current,
because l times w

00:11:39.755 --> 00:11:41.629
