00:21:01.165 --> 00:21:04.922
also the more difficult part,
which is, how do currents

00:21:04.922 --> 00:21:06.868
produce magnetic fields?
 

00:21:06.868 --> 00:21:09.720
Now we're going to the cause of
the magnetic field.

00:21:09.720 --> 00:21:13.598
At the end, everything is
produced by charges,

00:21:13.598 --> 00:21:16.618
microscopic charges,
but the formula for that is

00:21:16.618 --> 00:21:20.344
quite difficult to calculate
because if you look at all the

00:21:20.344 --> 00:21:22.333
charges,
and they're moving around

00:21:22.333 --> 00:21:25.648
producing magnetic field,
the field at any one location,

00:21:25.648 --> 00:21:28.269
because of the delay of
interaction,

00:21:28.269 --> 00:21:31.788
depends on what they were doing
at various times in the past.

00:21:31.788 --> 00:21:34.816
Just like electric fields are
also difficult to calculate if

00:21:34.816 --> 00:21:37.740
charges are moving because of
the relativistic theory that

00:21:37.740 --> 00:21:40.868
says you cannot communicate
instantly with another place.

00:21:40.868 --> 00:21:44.419
You can only do it at the speed
of light, so the field here

00:21:44.419 --> 00:21:47.785
depends on what was going on
earlier for the more remote

00:21:47.785 --> 00:21:48.519
charges.
 

00:21:48.519 --> 00:21:51.545
But in electrostatics,
we beat the problem by saying,

00:21:51.545 --> 00:21:54.279
"Look, none of these
charges ever moved.

00:21:54.279 --> 00:21:56.068
They've been there
forever."

00:21:56.068 --> 00:21:59.200
Then where they are now is
where they were before and we

00:21:59.200 --> 00:22:00.680
can calculate the field.
 

00:22:00.680 --> 00:22:05.244
The analogous thing for
magnetism is to say that if you

00:22:05.244 --> 00:22:09.048
have currents and the currents
are steady,

00:22:09.048 --> 00:22:14.067
then it's a case where the
magnetic field is also going to

00:22:14.067 --> 00:22:15.298
be constant.
 

00:22:15.298 --> 00:22:18.150
Remember, a steady current
doesn't mean there's no motion.

00:22:18.150 --> 00:22:21.327
It means the motion of these
charges round and round the loop

00:22:21.327 --> 00:22:22.069
is constant.
 

00:22:22.069 --> 00:22:24.420
It's not changing with time.
 

00:22:24.420 --> 00:22:29.542
Do not confuse a steady current
with a single particle moving at

00:22:29.542 --> 00:22:31.170
a steady velocity.
 

00:22:31.170 --> 00:22:33.869
That is not a steady current.
 

00:22:33.869 --> 00:22:36.710
You see the difference?
 

00:22:36.710 --> 00:22:39.904
Because if you sit at any one
point in a wire in a closed

00:22:39.904 --> 00:22:42.130
loop, the current is always the
same.

00:22:42.130 --> 00:22:44.167
If you have the instrument,
called the ammeter,

00:22:44.167 --> 00:22:46.516
that reads the current,
you can put it where you like,

00:22:46.516 --> 00:22:47.890
you'll get the same answer.
 

00:22:47.890 --> 00:22:50.243
But if a single charge is
carrying the current,

00:22:50.243 --> 00:22:53.108
there's a current here,
there's nothing anywhere else.

00:22:53.108 --> 00:22:57.328
There's a current only where
there is a charge.

00:22:57.328 --> 00:23:00.240
So it's like saying that when I
go on the freeway at 40 miles an

00:23:00.240 --> 00:23:02.659
